                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/154.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Mexican Chargé</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1907</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 112.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Governments of Honduras, Salvador, Guatemala,
                    and Costa Rica have notified this Government of their assent to the selection of
                    the Bureau of the American Republics as the place of meeting of the peace
                    conference of the Central American Republics.</p>
                <p>The minister of Nicaragua has not yet informed the department of the desire of
                    his Government in the matter; but as soon as he does, the department will have
                    pleasure in advising you thereof.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
